I made this last night around 2am, so forgive any blatant errors (tho, please, do point out any you see so I can fix them).  It's fairly simple, with the navigation (entries, friends list, etc...) at the top and each entry containing the following links at the bottom of it:
<li># comments - click to read
<li>comment - click to comment
<li>add to my memories - click to go to your "add to memories page"  --> this is your personal memories, not the community memories
<li>edit - click on your entries if you want to edit them; will bring you to your edit page
<li>tag it - click to edit/add tags to your own entries; will bring you to your tag page

<blockquote><b>ETA: Known Issue in Mozilla & Opera Browsers:</b>  <i>For some reason my perfectly innocent text links in equally innocent little divs (main menu at top) annoy the f#ck out of these browsers.  For you, this means you need to patiently hover around the text links a few extra seconds before you see the friendly little hand letting you know it's loaded (and you can click).  My apologies.  I have no idea why they won't load.  I mean, they're just text links! (grumbles)  IE -the world's worst browser- proves yets again it's still superior.  Mostly because -like VLC player- it loads any sh*t without raising a fuss.</i></blockquote>

Oh, and just so you know, this is a personal journal, not a community, which is why I don't have the user icons showing with each entry.  They WILL show up when the layout is loaded onto the community.

Snag it if you want, no need to credit & change whatever you want.  It's all free account overrides (read S1 -OLD- system).  The overrides are below (right click in textbox, select all, copy and paste into notepad or something).  Just use your own header (not the sneezeanime one, ok).

